The paper studies the dynamics of a marketplace and examines various marketing policies, which suggests that it could belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT) or Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. The use of a Mixed Multinomial Logit to model consumer preferences suggests that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.MA) sub-category. The focus on marketing policies and market segmentation suggests that it could belong to the Marketing (cs.MKT) or Computational Economics and Finance (cs.CE) sub-categories.
